The article discusses the progress made in implementing the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law signed by President Biden over a year ago. The law aims to make significant investments in the nation's infrastructure and competitiveness. President Biden highlighted in his State of the Union Address that the law would start repairs on 65,000 miles of roads and 1,500 bridges. Since then, the administration has exceeded these goals by launching over 3,700 bridge repair projects, beginning repairs on over 69,000 miles of roadway, and awarding funds for new clean transit and school buses. They have also made progress in water funding, EV charging networks, and high-speed internet deployment. The article emphasizes that these investments are positioning the United States to succeed in the 21st century.